text: Apha aequalis is a moth in the family Eupterotidae. It was described by Felder in 1874. It is found in Japan.BOLD Systems The wingspan is 45–59 mm.Japanese Moths The larvae feed on a wide range of plants, including Lonicera japonica.Biological Control of Weeds? ==References== Category:Moths described in 1874 Category:Eupterotinae
